    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'll try the digital microscope. i'm mainly worried about the loose patches. if the weave is too sparse, is there a specific way to measure the \"barrier\" quality? like, if we're talking about light transmission or breathability, how do we quantify how much \"space\" is actually between the fibers? i want to make sure the material is dense enough so nothing can pass through the weave unexpectedly.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
