      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To quantify the barrier quality, you should conduct a light transmittance test using a spectrophotometer. This measures the percentage of visible light passing through the fabric, with lower transmittance indicating a denser weave. Alternatively, for breathability, use a standardized Air Permeability Tester to measure how much air passes through the material per unit of time. These tests provide objective, quantifiable data regarding the weave's density and porosity.",
      "source": "target",
