      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i'll look into getting a spectrophotometer for the light transmission tests. one last thing though—when we talk about the \"integrity\" of the weave in luxury linens, we're often looking at how well the fabric resists external contaminants or even microscopic particles. if a weave is too loose, it's basically just an open mesh. at what point does the porosity become high enough that the fabric loses its \"protective\" quality against environmental debris or dust? is there a benchmark for how tight a weave needs to be to ensure it's a truly solid barrier?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
