      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There isn't one universal benchmark, as \"protective\" depends on the intended function (e.g., barrier against pollen versus small dust motes). However, for high-end luxury linens, a very low light transmittance reading (e.g., below 10%) generally suggests a compact barrier. For particle resistance, testing against standardized ISO dust challenge particles can provide a quantifiable benchmark for acceptable environmental filtration.",
      "source": "target",
